text: Mulepen Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Georgia. It is a tributary to the Ohoopee River. Mulepen Creek was named for a mule corral near its course. The name sometimes is spelled out as "Mule Pen Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Georgia (U.S. state) Category:Bodies of water of Emanuel County, Georgia Category:Bodies of water of Johnson County, Georgia
